Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Mummy breast cover
Description: Trapezoid-shaped mummy breast cover with from top to bottom: a winged solar disc framed by two falcon heads; a wesekh-collar framed by Osiris on the right and Sokar (falcon-headed mummy) on the left; two udjat-eyes at their feet; a winged scarab; a mummification scene by Anubis in the presence of mummiform Isis and Nephthys (canopic jars underneath the bed). The background is white, the edges are black.
